<item>
            <title>[HADOOP-6747] TestNetUtils fails on Mac OS X</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HADOOP-6747</link>
                <project id="12310240" key="HADOOP">Hadoop Common</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;TestNetUtils fails consistently after &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HADOOP-6722&quot; title=&quot;NetUtils.connect should check that it hasn&amp;#39;t connected a socket to itself&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HADOOP-6722&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HADOOP-6722&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; on Mac OS X Leopard 10.5.8:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;------------- Standard Error -----------------
local address: /127.0.0.1
local port: 64991
------------- ---------------- ---------------

Testcase: testAvoidLoopbackTcpSockets took 0.421 sec
        Caused an ERROR
Invalid argument
java.net.SocketException: Invalid argument
        at sun.nio.ch.Net.connect(Native Method)
        at sun.nio.ch.SocketChannelImpl.connect(SocketChannelImpl.java:507)
        at org.apache.hadoop.net.SocketIOWithTimeout.connect(SocketIOWithTimeout.java:192)
        at org.apache.hadoop.net.NetUtils.connect(NetUtils.java:369)
        at org.apache.hadoop.net.TestNetUtils.testAvoidLoopbackTcpSockets(TestNetUtils.java:46)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Although TCP spec seems to allow it, at least one implementation disallows this corner case. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Mac OS 10.5.8 (Leopard)&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
